**Brief description:**

Analyzer that checks whether
1. all public methods have been documented, or inherit a xml comment using `<inheritDoc />`.
    - if class inherits an interface/class, suggestion to use `<inheritDoc />` if it does not use it yet
1. the method signature (return + parameters) matches the xml comments
1. the `param name`s of the xml comment match the parameters of the method

**Languages applicable:**
I believe XML Comments are a C# thing?

